7. WARMUP-1 #7
problem: Warmup-1 > near_hundred 

"""
Given an int n, return True if it is within 10 of 100 or 200. Note: abs(num) computes the absolute value of a number. 
near_hundred(93) → True
near_hundred(90) → True
near_hundred(89) → False
"""

Note:

Absolute values:

abs(200-209)=9
abs(200-89)=111
abs(100-123)=23

Note: Math.abs(num) computes the absolute value of a number.

FINAL CODE SOLUTION:

def near_hundred(n):
  return ((abs(100 - n) <= 10) or (abs(200 - n) <= 10))

######################################################################################

8. WARMUP-1 #8
problem: Warmup-1 > pos_neg 

"""
Given 2 int values, return True if one is negative and one is positive. Unless the parameter "negative" is True, then they both must be negative. 
pos_neg(1, -1, False) → True
pos_neg(-1, 1, False) → True
pos_neg(1, 1, False) → False
"""

FINAL CODE SOLUTION:

def pos_neg(a, b, negative):
  if negative:
    return (a<0 and b<0)
  else:
    return ((a < 0 and b > 0) or (a > 0 and b < 0))

OTHER SOLUTION:

public boolean posNeg(int a, int b, boolean negative) {
  if (negative) {
    return (a<0 && b<0);
  }
  else {
    return ((a<0 && b>0) || (a>0 && b<0));
  }
}

